# BhardwajDeco Backend — Production-Level Architecture Upgrade

Upgrade the existing Express/MongoDB backend from a basic CRUD scaffold into a production-grade system with authentication, security hardening, AI-powered descriptions, and WhatsApp enquiry integration.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **API Keys Needed**: The AI description feature requires an OpenAI API key (`OPENAI_API_KEY`). The WhatsApp Twilio integration requires `TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID`, `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN`, and `TWILIO_WHATSAPP_FROM`. These are optional — the system gracefully degrades without them.

> [!WARNING]
> **Breaking Change**: All admin-facing routes (`POST /products`, `PUT /products/:id`, `DELETE /products/:id`, `GET /enquiries`, `POST /updates`, etc.) will now require a JWT `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header. The public routes (`GET /products`, `GET /products/:slug`, `POST /enquiry`, `GET /updates`) remain open.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Admin Credentials**: A single admin is created via `npm run seed`. Default credentials will be `admin@bhardwajdeco.com` / `BhardwajDeco@2026!`. You should change the password immediately after first login.

