### 4. Security Middleware Stack

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///c:/Users/svmbh/OneDrive/Desktop/BhardwajDeco/backend/src/server.js)

Integrate the full security middleware stack at the app level:

```js
import helmet from "helmet";
import rateLimit from "express-rate-limit";
import mongoSanitize from "express-mongo-sanitize";
import xssClean from "xss-clean";
import morgan from "morgan";
import compression from "compression";

// Security headers
app.use(helmet());

// Request logging
app.use(morgan("combined"));

// Response compression
app.use(compression());

// Rate limiting
app.use("/api/", rateLimit({
  windowMs: env.rateLimitWindowMs,
  max: env.rateLimitMax,
  message: { message: "Too many requests, please try again later" }
}));

// NoSQL injection prevention
app.use(mongoSanitize());

// XSS prevention
app.use(xssClean());
```

#### [NEW] `src/middleware/errorHandler.js`

Centralized error handler with:
- Mongoose validation errors → 400 with field-level messages
- Mongoose duplicate key → 409 conflict
- JWT errors → 401 unauthorized
- Cast errors → 400 bad request
- Generic → 500 with safe message (no stack in production)

#### [NEW] `src/middleware/validate.js`

Express-validator wrapper for reusable input validation chains:
- `validateProduct` — name, category, finish, description, heroImage required
- `validateEnquiry` — name, email (valid format), phone, productId required
- `validateLogin` — email + password required
- `validateUpdate` — title, excerpt, coverImage required

